{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3dc0014c-bb50-466d-a241-e9e13b2b1cad","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates crash reports when a process crashes:\n\n1. **User-level crashes** are saved to:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n\n2. **System-level crashes** go to:\n   ```\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n\nLook for `.ips` files named after your process (e.g., `YourApp-2026-05-02-*.ips`). These are JSON-formatted crash logs containing the thread backtraces, exception type, and faulting address.\n\nYou can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them with a GUI.\n\nTo get a core dump instead, run `ulimit -c unlimited` before launching your app — cores go to `/cores/core.<pid>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47366a62-b076-41b4-839f-c2ef4e92909e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app that crashed on macOS, without createdump available. This is a diagnostic question about .NET on macOS. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of macOS crash reporting.","outputTokens":267,"requestId":"5023:2C79E8:2885CB:320707:69F5544A"},"id":"0fc2d033-b659-4b11-bcf8-6f4ed24a6b30","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:33:09.672Z","parentId":"dadb2714-f8b7-484c-8c83-ba3481801e35"}
